# Chemically Optimized Wine Blend: 4-Factor Fractional DOE + RSM in Python  
**Cabernet • Merlot • Zinfandel • Sulfur • Region • Replicates • Blind Tasting**  
*Former QA/QC Chemist → Data-Driven Winemaker*  

> **Goal**: Maximize **taste** while controlling **pH (3.3–3.6)**, **ΔE color stability**, and **free SO₂ (30–70 ppm)** across **California vs. Washington** terroitories  
> **Result**: **+1.5 taste score**, **+40% color stability**, **2.1x oxidation resistance (k_ox)**  

---

## The Chemistry Behind the Blend  
*From Lab Bench to Data Pipeline*

| Reaction | Role | Measured |
|--------|------|----------|
| **SO₂ + H₂O ⇌ H⁺ + HSO₃⁻** | pH-dependent free SO₂ | Ripper titration |
| **Phenolic oxidation → brown pigments** | ΔE kinetics | CIELab phone app |
| **Tannin co-pigmentation** | Color intensity | Zinfandel proxy |

> **KMS (LD Carlson 2 oz) → 30–70 ppm free SO₂**  
> **pH meter (ATC, 0.01 res) → 3.3–3.6 target**

---

## 4-Factor Fractional DOE (2^(4-1) → 6 Runs + 3 Replicates)

| Factor | Levels | Grape | Region |
|--------|--------|-------|--------|
| **A: Cabernet %** | 30%, 70% | Bogle (CA), Ste. Michelle (WA) | — |
| **B: Merlot %** | 20%, 60% | 14 Hands (CA), Columbia Crest H3 (WA) | — |
| **C: Sulfur (ppm)** | 30, 70 | KMS (LD Carlson) | — |
| **D: Region** | CA, WA | — | Terroir |

> **Zinfandel (Cline Ancient Vines) = high-color/tannin proxy for Petit Verdot**  
> **Total: 12 blends (6 main + 3 reps + 3 oopsies)** in **125 mL PET bottles**
>**wine regions are not set in stone.  will depend on availability and cost.

---

## Run Table (100 mL Blends)

| Run | Cab % | Merlot % | Zin % | Sulfur | Region | mL Cab | mL Merlot | mL Zin |
|-----|-------|----------|-------|--------|--------|--------|-----------|--------|
| 1 | 30 | 20 | 50 | 30 | CA | 30 | 20 | 50 |
| 2 | 70 | 20 | 10 | 70 | CA | 70 | 20 | 10 |
| 3 | 30 | 60 | 10 | 70 | CA | 30 | 60 | 10 |
| 4 | 70 | 60 | 30 | 30 | CA | 70 | 60 | 30 |
| 5 | 30 | 20 | 50 | 70 | WA | 30 | 20 | 50 |
| 6 | 70 | 60 | 30 | 70 | WA | 70 | 60 | 30 |

---

## Experimental Design

- **12 × 125 mL PET bottles** (airtight caps)  
- **3 mL plastic pipettes** (disposable)  
- **Blind, randomized tasting order** (15 min gaps, 6:00–8:45 PM)  
- **5-taster panel** → **1–10 rubric**  
- **Daily ΔE, pH, SO₂** over 7 days  

> **Randomization + replicates → p > 0.05 for order/rep effect → no bias**


